longBusinessSummary: Greenbelt Resources Corporation designs, manufactures, operates, and sells modular systems that recycle food wastes, beverage, and cellulosic waste into sellable products. The company provides resource-to-ethanol technology solutions designed for localized processing of locally generated waste or energy crops into locally consumed ethanol, fertilizer, animal feed, electricity, and filtered and distilled water. It also offers technical support and monitoring services. Greenbelt Resources Corporation was formerly known as Originally New York, Inc. and changed its name to Greenbelt Resources Corporation in June 2007. The company was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Paso Robles, California. Greenbelt Resources Corporation operates as a subsidiary of James Monroe Capital Corporation.
